---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Teaching">

<div class="space-y-6">

  <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 shadow-sm">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">BC Curriculum</h1>
    <p class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-4">BC Ministry of Education · Grades 10–12</p>
    <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
      British Columbia's redesigned K–12 curriculum emphasizes deep conceptual understanding over
      rote procedure. Mathematics courses develop reasoning, number sense, and algebraic thinking
      across pathways suited to every student's destination — trades, university, or the workplace.
      Computer Studies builds the computational thinking and coding skills that are increasingly
      essential across every field. All courses are aligned with BC Ministry of Education
      requirements and the BC Graduation Program.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">

    <!-- Mathematics Column -->
    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 border-t-4 border-t-blue-600 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-5">Mathematics</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">

        <div>
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-400 mb-3">Grade 10</p>
          <ul class="space-y-4">
            <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
              <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm">Foundations of Mathematics &amp; Pre-calculus 10</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">The fork in the road — where students discover which mathematical path calls to them.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
              <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm">Workplace Mathematics 10</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">Because numbers don't stop being useful when you clock in.</p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-400 mb-3">Grade 11</p>
          <ul class="space-y-4">
            <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
              <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm">Foundations of Mathematics 11</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">Statistical thinking and financial literacy for a world full of data.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
              <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm">Pre-calculus 11</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">Where functions, trigonometry, and algebra sharpen into proper tools.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
              <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm">Workplace Mathematics 11</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">Math that pays dividends in the real economy.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
              <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm">History of Mathematics 11</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">The humans behind the theorems — mathematics as a living story.</p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-400 mb-3">Grade 12</p>
          <ul class="space-y-4">
            <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
              <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm">Apprenticeship Mathematics 12</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">Trades-ready numeracy: precision, measurement, and practical problem solving.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
              <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm">Foundations of Mathematics 12</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">Logic, probability, and the mathematics of decision-making.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
              <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm">Pre-calculus 12</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">The final runway before calculus — transformations, conics, and beyond.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
              <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm">Calculus 12</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">Rates, limits, and the mathematics of change. Newton would approve.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
              <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm">Geometry 12</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">Proofs, constructions, and the elegant logic of space.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
              <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm">Statistics 12</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">Data is everywhere. This course teaches you not to be fooled by it.</p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Computer Studies Column -->
    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 border-t-4 border-t-blue-600 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-5">Computer Studies</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">

        <div>
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-400 mb-3">Grade 10</p>
          <ul class="space-y-4">
            <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
              <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm">Computer Studies 10</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">Your first lines of code. The cursor blinks. Anything is possible.</p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-400 mb-3">Grade 11</p>
          <ul class="space-y-4">
            <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
              <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm">Computer Programming 11</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">From syntax to solutions — turning ideas into working programs.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
              <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm">Computer Science 11</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">Algorithms, complexity, and the mathematics powering modern software.</p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-slate-400 mb-3">Grade 12</p>
          <ul class="space-y-4">
            <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
              <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm">Computer Programming 12</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">Advanced techniques, real projects, and portfolio-worthy work.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
              <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm">Computer Information Systems 12</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">Databases, networks, and the infrastructure of the digital world.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-200">
              <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 text-sm">Computer Science 12</p>
              <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-0.5">Where mathematics and computation converge at the frontier.</p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

</div>

</Layout>
